    <h1>LDM @VERSION@</h1><br>
    <p> The Unidata Local Data Manager (LDM) is a collection of cooperating programs that select, capture, manage, and
    distribute arbitrary data products.  The system is designed for event-driven data distribution, and is currently
    used in the <a href="https://www.unidata.ucar.edu/projects/idd/"><b>Unidata Internet Data Distribution</b></a>
    (IDD) project. The LDM system includes network client and server programs and their shared protocols. The LDM
    supports flexible, site-specific configuration.</p>

